<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="343" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1452,1623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,1489,1512]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Remarks –</emphasis>
This species is very common in Mediterranean Sea (
<collectingCountry box="[1043,1142,1489,1512]" name="Croatia" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1161,1241,1489,1512]" name="Egypt" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1260,1350,1489,1512]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1370,1432,1489,1512]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,227,1526,1549]" name="Spain" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Spain</collectingCountry>
, Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[366,485,1526,1549]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[503,618,1526,1549]" name="Morocco" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Morocco</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[690,788,1526,1549]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Turkey</collectingCountry>
), being found in three other localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1344,1436,1526,1549]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[160,265,1563,1586]" country="Turkey" name="Istanbul" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Istanbul</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[332,435,1563,1586]" country="Turkey" name="Antalya" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Antalya</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Durucan, F. &amp; Boyaci, Y. O." box="[463,812,1563,1586]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" pagination="37 - 40" refId="ref2437" refString="Durucan, F. &amp; Boyaci, Y. O. (2016) Halacaropsis hirsuta (Acari: Halacaridae): First record for the Turkish Fauna. Journal of Egirdir Fisheries Faculty, 12: 37 - 40." type="journal article" year="2016">Durucan and Boyaci 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Durucan, F." box="[827,1018,1563,1586]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" pagination="352 - 373" refId="ref2398" refString="Durucan, F. (2020) Mediterranean and Black Sea marine halacarids (Halacaridae: Acari): A review. Journal of Black Sea / Mediterranean Environment, 26 (3): 352 - 373." type="journal article" year="2020">Durucan 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Length of idiosoma about 600 µm long and 440 µm wide (
<figureCitation box="[509,585,1600,1623]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[151,227,1247,1266]" captionTargetBox="[279,1302,500,1220]" captionTargetId="figure-239@3.[272,1317,486,1220]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Halacaropsis hirsuta (Trouessart, 1889) (deutonymph) – A. Dorsal view of idiosoma; B. Ventral view of idiosoma; C. Lateral view of gnathosoma; D. Ocular plate; E. Lateral view of leg I; F. Genitoanal plate (AP: anal plate; co: corneae; ep: eye pigment; gac: genital acetabula; pgs. perigenital setae). Scale bars: 50 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5236250" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5236250/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
